<HEADLINE>
`KOBE STOPPER' IS A NON-ISSUE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Kobe Bryant will face the self-proclaimed ``Kobe
stopper'' tonight in Seattle, but he's not exactly quivering at the
prospect. In fact, he can't believe anyone even considers Ruben
Patterson a relevant issue.
</P>
<P>
   ``You guys actually want to talk about that?'' Bryant said
incredulously, in response to reporters' questions.
</P>
<P>
   It might be the NBA's greatest non-rivalry. Patterson spent last
season with the Los Angeles Lakers and guarded Bryant daily in
practice, but no one thought much of it until he signed with the
Sonics in August, then declared, ``I dominated Kobe, and everybody
knew it. They called me the Kobe stopper. He hated when I guarded
him _ all the time.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant's reaction? ``I laughed. (Ticked) me off. I laughed,
though.''
</P>
<P>
   But Bryant, who was injured when the teams met in November,
looks forward to disproving Patterson's bold assertion.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sure, especially if he's guarding me,'' Bryant said. ``I don't
think they're going to have him guarding me. They'll probably put
Gary (Payton) on me, for obvious reasons. I don't think they
believe he's the `Kobestopper.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Not that Bryant was surprised at Patterson's bravado.
</P>
<P>
   ``Not really, because I know Rube. Rube likes to talk,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   According to Bryant, Patterson's successes against him were few,
and short-lived.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was funny. Days when I felt like competing real hard, I had
my way. Days when I didn't feel like being completely into it, he
would have his little moments or whatever and then he'd start
talking trash. And then (I) just nipped it in the bud, and that was
that.''
</P>
<P>
   Here to stay: At 3 p.m. today, Brian Shaw's nonguaranteed
one-year contract becomes guaranteed for the season, and it's clear
he's earned a roster spot for the season. Shaw was signed in the
wake of Bryant's broken hand in October, and he continues to
provide security and veteran experience in the guard corps.
</P>
<P>
   Ankle problems dogged Shaw in late December, but coach Phil
Jackson has started to rely on him again recently, especially with
Derek Fisher struggling with his shot. Shaw had a season-high eight
assists against the Clippers on Wednesday and scored seven points
against the Clippers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We knew what we wanted from Brian when we got him,'' Jackson
said. ``I basically said, `You're here to plug a hole that's left
by Kobe Bryant's injury.... We need a big guard, especially in the
kind of system I like to run. If it works out, you may be here for
the year, but I can't guarantee anything.' So we started out at a
premise at that level, and he just continued to fulfill the
promise. He's going to be a team player and a good one.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
