<HEADLINE>
LIBERTIES: HIS HEARTBREAK HOTEL 
</HEADLINE>
  (nk) 
 By MAUREEN DOWD    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The fun at the Chappaqua hacienda is over. Bill
Clinton has finished the heady business of unpacking that one old
table he hadn't seen in 17 years. Now he faces a new life here as
President Lonely Guy.
</P>
<P>
   Restless and rattling around the empty-nest White House, he
begins dialing. This is the official log of calls he made on his
first night home alone:
</P>
<P>
   6 p.m. Call to Hillary in Chappaqua: ``Honey, did you take my
Kenny G CD? I can't find it anywhere. I'm so lonesome I could cry.
This place is Heartbreak Hotel. Just remember, whatever you need me
to do, Madame Candidate ...''
</P>
<P>
   6:15 p.m. Call to Harold Ickes in Georgetown: ``Harold, you were
right to make me go up to Chappaqua that first night Hillary moved
in. But, look, man, about that other thing you want me to do, the
cook-off with Donna Hanover on the food channel? I don't know about
that. Wearing an apron and all ...''
</P>
<P>
   7 p.m. Call to Martin Sheen in Hollywood: ``Hey, President
Bartlett? This is President Clinton. I just wanted to tell you how
much I am lovin' the way you play me in `West Wing.' What's your
fax number? I've got some notes for your next show ...''
</P>
<P>
   7:45 p.m. Call to Jenny Craig office in D.C.: ``I've been
watching some of your new ads, and that stuff you sell really seems
to work. I've gained 18 pounds and I am fat as a wood tick. With
Hillary gone, it's surely going to get worse. She made me eat baked
french fries. Have you ever heard of such a thing? Does your plan
allow fried foods? ...''
</P>
<P>
   8 p.m. Call to Jimmy Carter in Atlanta: ``Hey, Jimmy. No matter
what you read, I am not taking that job at Lazard Freres for $10
million. I am modeling my life after the presidency on you. Do you
know where I can get a tool belt? ...''
</P>
<P>
   8:15 p.m. Call to Vernon Jordan in New York: ``Hey, buddy. A
measly $10 million a year for a president who got the economy
cookin' again? You're low ballin' me, Vernon. You tell
Laissez-Faire I won't do it for less than $20 mil. Dreamworks
offered me that already ...''
</P>
<P>
   9 p.m. Call to David Geffen in Hollywood: ``David? Oh, sorry,
who are you? The personal trainer and Kabbalah consultant? What's
your name? Listen up, Matt, can you put in a good word for me with
David? I'm still waiting for that offer ...''
</P>
<P>
   9:30 p.m. Call to Al Gore in New Hampshire: ``Hel-lo-o-o? Is
this the same Al Gore who was around in '93 when we were getting
killed over gays in the military? You are a fortunate son, Al, that
Bradley is such a supercilious prig ...''
</P>
<P>
   9:45 p.m. Call to Bill Bradley in Iowa: ``Hey, Bill. Between you
and I, I just wanted you to know that, no matter what Al says,
Hillary and me both think your health care plan is real good ...''
</P>
<P>
   10 p.m. Call to Richard Gephardt in Sterling, Va.: ``Dick, did I
wake you? I'm sorry. I know you're scrappin' for every seat and I
could take that one in Arkansas. It would be a privilege to serve
under you because you'd be a great speaker and I would support you
1,000 percent ...''
</P>
<P>
   10:30 p.m. Call to Dick Morris in New York: ``Hey, man, we need
to start polling right away. If I win that Arkansas House seat in
2002, could I knock off Gephardt as speaker? So, what do you think
is better for my approval rating: one night a week in New York, two
nights a week in New York, or can I get away with no nights at all
in that snakebit suburb? ...''
</P>
<P>
   Midnight. Call to Jennifer Lopez in Miami: ``Jennifer? Hey, it's
your president callin'. You got a bum rap. Puffy is 10 miles of bad
road. I'm calling to enlist your help in an important new gun
control campaign. You could spread our message, `Don't spend
Saturday night with a Saturday night special.' Why don't I send an
Air Force plane for you? ...''
</P>
<P>
   12:30 p.m. Call to Puff Daddy in the Hamptons: ``Puffy? The
witch set you up. I'm going to call Janet Reno right away. Hey, you
know where I could get some TLC? ...''
</P>
<P>
   1:30 a.m. Call to Jack Nicholson in L.A.: ``Jack! My main man!
The coast is clear. Nurse Ratched has flown the nest. She thinks
it's my turn to bake cookies. Mi casa blanca, su casa blanca. Hey,
do you happen to have Jewel's number? ...''
</P>
<P>
   2:00 a.m. Call to Domino's Pizza in D.C.: ``Can y'all deliver
100 large pies with extra cheese right away? Great. I'm in McLean,
Virginia, and my name is Ken Starr, S-T-A-R-R.''
</P>
</TEXT>
