<P>
   CLINTON-MIDEAST _ WASHINGTON _ After years spent trying to end
war in the Middle East, President Clinton has begun preparing
Americans for the price of peace. Any agreement reached among
Israel and its Arab neighbors, in other words, will require
Americans to spend billions of dollars on military, economic and
humanitarian aid. U.S. troops might also be needed as part of a
larger United Nations force to police the peace. Analysts' best
estimates on what Americans should brace for amid Clinton's
full-court press to broker a comprehensive Mideast peace accord
before he leaves office next year. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
