   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-EXILES _ MIAMI _ Outside South Florida, young Elian
Gonzalez's story seems sad but simple to many Americans: Blood ties
are more important than politics, so in the best interests of the
child, send him back to his father. But for Cuban-Americans _ or
exiles, as they are called _ the issue is much more complex, and
emotional. For many of them, politics isn't about abstract policies
or ideas. It is intensely personal, born of pain, loss and
separation. It is about morals and principles. And passion.
(MWilliams, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED in (i) International and (w) Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   EDWARDS _ BATON ROUGE _ He's been on trial twice before, and
slipped out of prosecutors' grasps, but a lot of observers think
four-time Louisiana Gov. Edwin ''Fast Eddie'' Edwards might see the
inside of a jail cell this time. He goes on trial Monday on federal
charges of extorting money in exchange for riverboat casino
licenses when he was governor and afterward. The trial is expected
to last 3 months and provide as much entertainment as the very
strict Judge Polozola will allow. (Konigsmark, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FLAGMARCH _ COLUMBIA, S.C. _ Coverage of South Carolina Heritage
Coalition and Heritage Celebration 2000 in support of flying the
Confederate flag over the Statehouse. (Burritt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
