</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sloan, Issel bristle
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Don't invite Utah's Jerry Sloan and Denver's Dan Issel
to your party. The feud started last week when the Jazz broke open
a tight game to lead by 20 with two minutes left and left Karl
Malone, John Stockton and Bryon Russell in the game against Nuggets
scrubs.
</P>
<P>
   After Stockton threw ahead to Malone for a fast-break dunk,
Issel stormed to midcourt and yelled at Sloan, ``I'll remember
this.''
</P>
<P>
   Sloan ambled up and asked, ``Why?''
</P>
<P>
   Issel retorted, ``Kiss my (bleep).''
</P>
<P>
   Afterward, Issel said, ``That's all right. I shouldn't have
reacted the way I did. But I have a long memory.''
</P>
<P>
   And Sloan said, ``I guess he thought I was keeping (starters) in
there too long. The clock hadn't stopped when I planned to put
(substitutes) in there. I told them to take a foul; they didn't
take a foul.
</P>
<P>
   ``So he remembered it. I remember when he quit right in the
middle of the year, too, when he was coaching. ... I've never done
anything to run the score up. And I've been here long enough to
know I certainly wouldn't quit on anybody.''
</P>
<P>
   ABDUR-RAHIM'S CLOUT
</P>
<P>
   In not-so-veiled terms, Vancouver's newspapers are suggesting
Shareef Abdur-Rahim influenced the club's decision to oust coach
Brian Hill. The former Wheeler High star says that's not the case,
but that he does prefer the replacement, Lionel Hollins.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't have anything to do with what Brian was doing or
wasn't doing. It's just how I'm feeling since Lionel took over _
the things `Train' has us doing, the way we're going out and
playing as a team and conducting ourselves. It's the best I've felt
playing basketball in a long time.''
</P>
<P>
   Abdur-Rahim also remains loyal to general manager Stu Jackson,
saying his ``future is a concern of mine. When I re-signed (six
years, $71 million), the owner kind of assured me that Stu was
their guy and I've always said Stu is the reason I re-signed here.
I'd feel like I was misled'' if Jackson is fired.
</P>
<P>
   LAYUPS
</P>
<P>
   It could only happen in Clipperville: Michael Olowokandi misses
practice one day after Maurice Taylor rips his work ethic. Derek
Anderson doesn't show because he thinks coach Chris Ford gave the
club the day off. Lamar Odom isn't there because Charlie Jones had
an excused absence, and Jones drives Odom to practice because the
rookie does not have a driver's license. ...
</P>
<P>
   So, maybe it was a fit of pique that drove Shaquille O'Neal to
resist his agents' pleas and say no to the Olympics. ``The last
time I played, I only played two minutes and the coach (Lenny
Wilkens) put in David Robinson the whole game. I'm not going
through that (stuff) anymore.'' ... The Lakers went 14-1 last
month, their best December mark since 1971-72, when the Wilt
Chamberlain-Jerry West squad went 16-0 en route to their record 33
wins in a row.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
