<P>
   HIDDEN-HILLS (Los Angeles) -- It's the most exclusive, priciest
community in L.A.'s San Fernando Valley, home to celebrities and
CEOs, where a house that sells for $1 million is considered a
fixer-upper. Those who live in the 625-home city compare it to an
idyllic suburb of yesteryear, where everbody knows each other -
except for a few celebs who crave privacy - and kids feel safe
playing in the streets. The crime rate in Hidden Hills is almost
zero, thanks to gates, cameras and patrolling guards. It's almost
so isolated and perfect that one resident compared it to something
out of ``The Stepford Wives.'' Among celebrities that own homes
there, according to other residents: Sinbad, Alex Van Halen, Lisa
Marie Presley, Bob Eubanks, Beau Bridges. By Harrison Sheppard
(Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news wires.)
